==Gameplay==
Gameplay takes place in three sections. First, a territory to attack is selected from the campaign screen; next the player is taken to the territory, where he battles through hordes of themed aggressors on a [[Side-scrolling video game|side-scrolling]] landscape to reach a castle, which he must also conquer; finally the player faces the master of the castle – a wizard with four spell-casting tentacle arms – whom he must defeat by firing magic at him whilst avoiding the spells that the wizard fires back. On defeating the master of the castle the player wins the territory and returns to the campaign screen to select the next territory to attack.

==Reception==
''Onslaught'' received mixed reviews on its release. Whilst ''[[The Games Machine]]'' gave it a score of 95% and rated it a "Top Game"<ref name='TGMReview'>{{cite news | title=Onslaught | date=December 1989 | publisher=[[Newsfield Publications Ltd]] | url =http://amr.abime.net/review_33800 | work =[[The Games Machine]] | pages =72–73 | access-date = 2009-02-25}}</ref> and [[Zzap!64|Zzap!]] scored it 85%,<ref name='Zzap!Review'>{{cite news | first=Stuart | last=Wynne |author2=Hogg, Robin | title=Onslaught | date=February 1990 | publisher=Newsfield Publications Ltd | url =http://www.zzap64.co.uk/cgi-bin/displaypage.pl?issue=58&page=71&magazine=zzap | work =[[Zzap!64|Zzap!]] | pages =71 | access-date = 2009-02-25}}</ref> ''Your Amiga'' gave it 54%,<ref name='YourAmigaReview'>{{cite news | first=Gordon | last=Hamlett | title=Onslaught | date=January 1990 | url =http://amr.abime.net/amr_popup_picture.php?src=your_amiga/magscans/ya_1990_01/031.jpg&c=75778&n=1&filesize=501145 | work =Your Amiga | pages =31 | access-date = 2009-02-25}}</ref> and Sweden's Datormagazin awarded it just 3/10.<ref name='Datormagazin'>{{cite news | first=Mathias | last=Thinsz | title=Onslaught | date=January 1990 | url =http://guildserver.co.uk/AMR/dator/dm_1990_01_1990-02/008.jpg | work =Datormagazin | pages =8 | access-date = 2009-02-25 | language = sv}}</ref> ''[[Mega (magazine)|Mega]]'' placed the game at #8 in their list of the 10 Worst Mega Drive Games of All Time.<ref>Mega magazine issue #1, page 85, [[Future Publishing]], Oct 1992</ref>

